08/06/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A peacekeeping unit left for Iraq on Friday (6 June) to join the international mission there. 
Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski described Macedonia's participation as a confirmation of the country's commitment to joining NATO and strengthening efforts against terrorism. 
The 28-strong unit includes members of the special units "Scorpions" and "Wolves" and is to guard facilities and roads near the town of Taji together with the 4th American infantry division. 
The Macedonian contingent also includes a nine-member medical team. 
(MIA- 06/06/03)
